./quickaibuy_auto_diagnose_20260326_081212.log:295:./node_modules/msgpackr/README.md:330:Msgpackr is designed to work well with reusable buffers. Allocating new buffers can be relatively expensive, so if you have Node addons, it can be much faster to reuse buffers and use memcpy to copy data into existing buffers. Then msgpackr `unpack` can be executed on the same buffer, with new data, and optionally take a second paramter indicating the effective size of the available data in the buffer.
